---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
import Header from "../components/Header.astro";
import Footer from "../components/Footer.astro";
import "../styles/global.css";
---

<Layout title="Documentation - Helpmaton">
  <Header />
  <main class="min-h-screen bg-neutral-950 p-8 py-16">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
      <div class="mb-12 text-center">
        <h1 class="text-display-2 font-display text-neutral-100 mb-4 text-glow">
          Documentation
        </h1>
        <p class="text-lg text-neutral-400">
          Everything you need to know about Helpmaton
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="space-y-6">
        <!-- Prominent FAQ Link -->
        <section
          class="bg-gradient-to-r from-primary-500 to-primary-600 rounded-lg shadow-neon-lg p-8 border border-primary-400/50 text-neutral-950"
        >
          <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
            <div class="text-4xl">❓</div>
            <div class="flex-1">
              <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-neutral-950 mb-3">
                Quick Answers to Common Questions
              </h2>
              <p class="text-neutral-800 mb-4 text-lg">
                Looking for quick answers? Check out our FAQ page covering setup, agents, workspaces, billing, API, and more.
              </p>
              <a
                href="/faq"
                class="inline-block bg-neutral-950 text-primary-400 px-6 py-3 font-semibold rounded-lg hover:bg-neutral-900 transition-colors shadow-neon hover:scale-105 transform transition-transform border border-primary-400/50"
              >
                View FAQ →
              </a>
            </div>
          </div>
        </section>

        <section
          class="bg-neutral-900 rounded-lg shadow-soft p-6 border border-primary-500/20"
        >
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-neutral-100 mb-4">
            Getting Started
          </h2>
          <p class="mb-4 text-neutral-400">
            New to Helpmaton? Start here! We'll guide you through creating your
            first workspace, setting up agents, and uploading documents.
          </p>
          <a
            href="/getting-started"
            class="inline-block bg-primary-500 text-neutral-950 px-4 py-2 font-medium rounded-lg hover:bg-primary-400 transition-colors text-sm shadow-neon border border-primary-400/50"
          >
            Read Getting Started Guide →
          </a>
        </section>

        <section
          class="bg-neutral-900 rounded-lg shadow-soft p-6 border border-primary-500/20"
        >
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-neutral-100 mb-4">
            Working with Agents
          </h2>
          <p class="mb-4 text-neutral-400">
            Learn how to create, configure, and manage your AI agents. From
            basic setup to advanced configurations, we've got you covered.
          </p>
          <ul
            class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 text-sm text-neutral-400 ml-4"
          >
            <li>Creating your first agent</li>
            <li>Configuring agent personalities</li>
            <li>Setting up agent workflows</li>
            <li>Managing multiple agents</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section
          class="bg-neutral-900 rounded-lg shadow-soft p-6 border border-primary-500/20"
        >
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-neutral-100 mb-4">
            Agent Memory System
          </h2>
          <p class="mb-4 text-neutral-400">
            Agents remember important facts, people, and events from
            conversations through an advanced memory system. This enables context-aware responses informed by past
            interactions.
          </p>
          <ul
            class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 text-sm text-neutral-400 ml-4"
          >
            <li>Advanced memory system organized by time periods</li>
            <li>
              Progressive summarization (daily, weekly, monthly, quarterly,
              yearly)
            </li>
            <li>Smart search for memory retrieval</li>
            <li>
              Plan-based memory retention (Free: 48h working + 30d summaries,
              Pro: 240h + 120d)
            </li>
            <li>Automatic memory cleanup and management</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section
          class="bg-neutral-900 rounded-lg shadow-soft p-6 border border-primary-500/20"
        >
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-neutral-100 mb-4">
            Workspaces
          </h2>
          <p class="mb-4 text-neutral-400">
            Organize your AI agents into workspaces. Each workspace is like a
            separate container with its own settings, credits, and team members.
          </p>
          <div
            class="mb-4 p-4 bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg"
          >
            <p class="text-sm text-neutral-700">
              <strong>Note:</strong> Workspace credits are used for AI provider calls
              (OpenAI, Anthropic, etc.), not for platform subscription costs. You
              can either provide your own API keys or purchase credits through Helpmaton.
            </p>
          </div>
          <ul
            class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 text-sm text-neutral-400 ml-4"
          >
            <li>Creating and managing workspaces</li>
            <li>Setting spending limits (for AI provider costs)</li>
            <li>Adding your own API keys or purchasing credits</li>
            <li>
              Team collaboration and subscription sharing (Pro plans support
              unlimited managers)
            </li>
            <li>Workspace permissions</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section
          class="bg-neutral-900 rounded-lg shadow-soft p-6 border border-primary-500/20"
        >
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-neutral-100 mb-4">
            Documents
          </h2>
          <p class="mb-4 text-neutral-400">
            Upload and organize documents to give your agents knowledge. Learn
            about supported formats, organization, and best practices.
          </p>
          <ul
            class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 text-sm text-neutral-400 ml-4"
          >
            <li>Uploading documents</li>
            <li>Organizing with folders</li>
            <li>Supported file formats</li>
            <li>Document management tips</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section
          class="bg-neutral-900 rounded-lg shadow-soft p-6 border border-primary-500/20"
        >
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-neutral-100 mb-4">
            Usage Analytics & Monitoring
          </h2>
          <p class="mb-4 text-neutral-400">
            Comprehensive usage tracking and monitoring tools to help you
            understand and optimize your AI spending. View detailed analytics
            across all dimensions of your usage.
          </p>
          <ul
            class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 text-sm text-neutral-400 ml-4"
          >
            <li>
              Usage tracking (all AI request types)
            </li>
            <li>Daily and hourly aggregation</li>
            <li>Historical data with date range filtering</li>
            <li>Per-workspace and per-agent breakdowns</li>
            <li>Cost tracking and budget monitoring</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section
          class="bg-neutral-900 rounded-lg shadow-soft p-6 border border-primary-500/20"
        >
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-neutral-100 mb-4">
            Web Search & Content Extraction
          </h2>
          <p class="mb-4 text-neutral-400">
            Give your agents access to real-time, up-to-date information beyond
            their training data. Enable web search and content extraction tools
            to make your AI assistants more capable and current.
          </p>
          <div class="mb-4 space-y-4 text-sm text-neutral-400">
            <div>
              <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-100 mb-2">
                Web Search (search_web)
              </h3>
              <p class="mb-2">
                Agents can search the web for current information, news,
                articles, and research. Perfect for finding the latest
                developments, answering questions about recent events, or
                discovering new resources. Search results include titles, URLs,
                content snippets, and relevance scores.
              </p>
              <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-1 ml-4">
                <li>Find current information that isn't in training data</li>
                <li>Answer questions about recent events and developments</li>
                <li>Discover new articles and resources</li>
                <li>Get real-time information for research assistants</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
            <div>
              <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-100 mb-2">
                Content Extraction (fetch_web)
              </h3>
              <p class="mb-2">
                Extract and summarize content from any web page URL. Agents can
                read and understand specific web pages, analyze articles,
                extract key information, and provide insights from any online
                content.
              </p>
              <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-1 ml-4">
                <li>Extract main content from web pages</li>
                <li>Summarize articles and online resources</li>
                <li>Analyze web content for insights</li>
                <li>Perfect for content analysis workflows</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
            <div>
              <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-100 mb-2">Pricing</h3>
              <p class="mb-2">
                All plans include                 <strong class="text-primary-400"
                  >10 free web search calls per 24 hours</strong
                >. Additional calls are billed at <strong class="text-primary-400"
                  >$0.008 per call</strong
                >. This gives you access to real-time information at a
                transparent, cost-effective rate.
              </p>
              <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-1 ml-4">
                <li>Free tier: 10 calls per 24 hours included</li>
                <li>
                  Paid tiers: 10 free calls per day, then $0.008 per additional
                  call
                </li>
                <li>
                  Perfect for research assistants, news monitoring, and content
                  analysis
                </li>
              </ul>
            </div>
            <div>
              <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-100 mb-2">
                Enabling Web Search
              </h3>
              <p class="mb-2">
                Enable web search and content extraction per-agent with simple
                toggle switches:
              </p>
              <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-1 ml-4">
                <li>Go to your agent's configuration page</li>
                <li>Find the "Web Search" and "Content Extraction" toggles</li>
                <li>
                  Enable the features you want (web search, content extraction,
                  or both)
                </li>
                <li>Your agents can now access real-time information!</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
          </div>
          <p class="text-xs text-neutral-500 mt-3">
            Web search and content extraction are powerful tools that extend
            your agents' capabilities beyond their training data, enabling them
            to provide current, relevant information for research, news
            monitoring, and content analysis workflows.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section
          class="bg-neutral-900 rounded-lg shadow-soft p-6 border border-primary-500/20"
        >
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-neutral-100 mb-4">
            Webhooks & Integrations
          </h2>
          <p class="mb-4 text-neutral-400">
            Connect Helpmaton to your existing tools and workflows. Set up
            webhooks, integrate with APIs, and automate your processes.
          </p>
          <ul
            class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 text-sm text-neutral-400 ml-4"
          >
            <li>Setting up webhooks</li>
            <li>Real-time streaming with Server-Sent Events (SSE)</li>
            <li>Webhook events and payloads</li>
            <li>Integration examples</li>
            <li>Troubleshooting webhooks</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section
          class="bg-neutral-900 rounded-lg shadow-soft p-6 border border-primary-500/20"
        >
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-neutral-100 mb-4">
            Built-in Tools & External Integrations
          </h2>
          <p class="mb-4 text-neutral-400">
            Agents come with a comprehensive set of built-in tools and can be
            extended with external integrations to connect to
            external APIs and services.
          </p>
          <div class="mb-4 space-y-4 text-sm text-neutral-400">
            <div>
              <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-100 mb-2">
                Built-in Tools
              </h3>
              <p class="mb-2">
                Every agent has access to these powerful tools out of the box:
              </p>
              <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-1 ml-4">
                <li>
                  <strong>Document Search:</strong> Smart search across
                  workspace documents
                </li>
                <li>
                  <strong>Memory Search:</strong> Recall past conversations and information
                  from the agent's memory system
                </li>
                <li>
                  <strong>Web Search:</strong> Search the web for current information,
                  news, and articles
                </li>
                <li>
                  <strong>Web Fetch:</strong> Extract and summarize content from any
                  web page URL
                </li>
                <li>
                  <strong>Email Sending:</strong> Send emails using workspace email
                  connections
                </li>
                <li>
                  <strong>Notification Sending:</strong> Send notifications to Discord
                  channels (with API support for Slack)
                </li>
                <li>
                  <strong>Agent Delegation:</strong> Agents can delegate tasks to
                  other agents in the workspace
                </li>
              </ul>
            </div>
            <div>
              <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-100 mb-2">
                External Integrations (Extensibility)
              </h3>
              <p class="mb-2">
                Extend your agents' capabilities with external integrations. Connect to external APIs, databases, and custom
                tools to enable powerful integrations.
              </p>
              <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-1 ml-4">
                <li>What are external integrations?</li>
                <li>Configuring external connections with custom authentication</li>
                <li>Enabling external integrations per-agent</li>
                <li>Authentication and security</li>
                <li>Use cases and examples</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
          </div>
        </section>

        <section
          class="bg-neutral-900 rounded-lg shadow-soft p-6 border border-primary-500/20"
        >
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-neutral-100 mb-4">
            Google Workspace Integration
          </h2>
          <p class="mb-4 text-neutral-400">
            Connect your agents to Gmail, Google Calendar, and Google Drive with easy OAuth setup. Just connect your Google account—no complex configuration or API keys needed. Your agents can manage your calendar, read and search emails, and access Drive files.
          </p>
          <div class="mb-4 space-y-4 text-sm text-neutral-400">
            <div>
              <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-100 mb-2">
                Easy OAuth Setup
              </h3>
              <p class="mb-2">
                Setting up Google Workspace integration is simple and secure:
              </p>
              <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-1 ml-4">
                <li>Go to "Integrations" in your workspace settings</li>
                <li>Create an MCP server for the Google service you want (Gmail, Calendar, or Drive)</li>
                <li>Click "Connect Google Account" and sign in</li>
                <li>Grant the necessary permissions</li>
                <li>Enable the connection for your agents</li>
              </ul>
              <p class="mt-2 text-xs text-neutral-500">
                All connections use secure OAuth 2.0 authentication to keep your data private and secure.
              </p>
            </div>
            <div>
              <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-100 mb-2">
                Gmail Integration
              </h3>
              <p class="mb-2">
                Connect agents to Gmail accounts via OAuth, enabling agents to:
              </p>
              <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-1 ml-4">
                <li>List and search emails using Gmail's powerful search syntax</li>
                <li>Read full email content including headers, body, and attachments</li>
                <li>Search using queries like "from:example@gmail.com", "subject:meeting", "is:unread"</li>
                <li>Perfect for email management, filtering, and automated email workflows</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
            <div>
              <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-100 mb-2">
                Google Calendar Integration
              </h3>
              <p class="mb-2">
                Connect agents to Google Calendar for full calendar management:
              </p>
              <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-1 ml-4">
                <li>List events and search by query</li>
                <li>Read event details including attendees, times, and descriptions</li>
                <li>Create new events and update existing ones</li>
                <li>Delete events when needed</li>
                <li>Perfect for scheduling assistants, meeting coordinators, and calendar management workflows</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
            <div>
              <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-100 mb-2">
                Google Drive Integration
              </h3>
              <p class="mb-2">
                Give agents access to files stored in Google Drive:
              </p>
              <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-1 ml-4">
                <li>Read text files and documents</li>
                <li>Access Google Docs (exported as plain text)</li>
                <li>Read Google Sheets (exported as CSV)</li>
                <li>Access Google Slides (exported as plain text)</li>
                <li>Ideal for document analysis, data extraction, and content management workflows</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
          </div>
          <p class="text-xs text-neutral-500 mt-3">
            Google Workspace integrations enable powerful automation workflows where your agents can interact with your Google services seamlessly. See the <a href="https://github.com/djinilabs/helpmaton/blob/main/docs/mcp-servers.md" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-primary-600 hover:text-primary-700 underline">MCP Servers documentation</a> for detailed setup instructions.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section
          class="bg-neutral-900 rounded-lg shadow-soft p-6 border border-primary-500/20"
        >
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-neutral-100 mb-4">
            Notion Integration
          </h2>
          <p class="mb-4 text-neutral-400">
            Connect your agents to Notion with easy OAuth setup. Just connect your Notion account—no complex configuration or API keys needed. Your agents can read and search pages, create and update content, query databases, and manage your Notion workspace.
          </p>
          <div class="mb-4 space-y-4 text-sm text-neutral-400">
            <div>
              <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-100 mb-2">
                Easy OAuth Setup
              </h3>
              <p class="mb-2">
                Setting up Notion integration is simple and secure:
              </p>
              <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-1 ml-4">
                <li>Go to "Integrations" in your workspace settings</li>
                <li>Create an MCP server and select "Notion"</li>
                <li>Click "Connect Notion Account" and sign in</li>
                <li>Grant the necessary permissions</li>
                <li>Enable the connection for your agents</li>
              </ul>
              <p class="mt-2 text-xs text-neutral-500">
                All connections use secure OAuth authentication to keep your data private and secure.
              </p>
            </div>
            <div>
              <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-100 mb-2">
                Page Management
              </h3>
              <p class="mb-2">
                Agents can read, search, create, and update Notion pages:
              </p>
              <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-1 ml-4">
                <li>Read any page by its ID, including properties, metadata, and content</li>
                <li>Search for pages, databases, and data sources across your workspace</li>
                <li>Create new pages with simplified parameters (name and content) or advanced options</li>
                <li>Update page properties and content</li>
                <li>Append blocks (paragraphs, headings, lists) to existing pages</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
            <div>
              <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-100 mb-2">
                Database Management
              </h3>
              <p class="mb-2">
                Agents can query and manage Notion databases:
              </p>
              <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-1 ml-4">
                <li>Query databases with filters and sorts to find specific records</li>
                <li>Create new pages in databases with properties matching the schema</li>
                <li>Update database page properties</li>
                <li>Perfect for knowledge management, project tracking, and data workflows</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
          </div>
          <p class="text-xs text-neutral-500 mt-3">
            Notion integration enables powerful knowledge management workflows where your agents can interact with your Notion workspace seamlessly. Perfect for documentation assistants, knowledge bases, and content management. See the <a href="https://github.com/djinilabs/helpmaton/blob/main/docs/mcp-servers.md" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-primary-600 hover:text-primary-700 underline">MCP Servers documentation</a> for detailed setup instructions.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section
          class="bg-neutral-900 rounded-lg shadow-soft p-6 border border-primary-500/20"
        >
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-neutral-100 mb-4">
            Error Tracking
          </h2>
          <p class="mb-4 text-neutral-400">
            Conversations automatically persist and display errors when AI
            requests fail, making it easy to identify and debug issues in your AI
            agent workflows.
          </p>
          <ul
            class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 text-sm text-neutral-400 ml-4"
          >
            <li>Automatic error persistence in conversations</li>
            <li>Detailed error messages with stack traces</li>
            <li>Provider information and metadata for debugging</li>
            <li>Error badges in conversation lists for quick identification</li>
            <li>Detailed error views with full context</li>
            <li>Historical error tracking across conversations</li>
          </ul>
          <p class="mt-4 text-sm text-neutral-500">
            Error tracking works automatically - no configuration needed. When
            AI requests fail, errors are immediately visible in your conversation
            interface.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section
          class="bg-neutral-900 rounded-lg shadow-soft p-6 border border-primary-500/20"
        >
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-neutral-100 mb-4">
            Agent Delegation
          </h2>
          <p class="mb-4 text-neutral-400">
            Agents can delegate tasks to other agents in the workspace, enabling
            complex multi-agent workflows and sophisticated task orchestration.
          </p>
          <ul
            class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 text-sm text-neutral-400 ml-4"
          >
            <li>How agent delegation works</li>
            <li>Setting up multi-agent workflows</li>
            <li>Task distribution and coordination</li>
            <li>Specialized agent teams</li>
            <li>Use cases for agent collaboration</li>
            <li>Best practices for delegation patterns</li>
          </ul>
          <p class="mt-4 text-sm text-neutral-500">
            Agent delegation enables you to build sophisticated systems where
            agents collaborate, share responsibilities, and handle specialized
            tasks.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section
          class="bg-neutral-900 rounded-lg shadow-soft p-6 border border-primary-500/20"
        >
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-neutral-100 mb-4">
            Email Sending
          </h2>
          <p class="mb-4 text-neutral-400">
            Configure email authentication for your workspace to enable agents
            to send emails using workspace email connections.
          </p>
          <ul
            class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 text-sm text-neutral-400 ml-4"
          >
            <li>Configuring workspace email connections</li>
            <li>Setting up SMTP authentication</li>
            <li>Using the email sending tool in agents</li>
            <li>Email templates and formatting</li>
            <li>Best practices for agent email communications</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section
          class="bg-neutral-900 rounded-lg shadow-soft p-6 border border-primary-500/20"
        >
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-neutral-100 mb-4">
            Chat Platform Bot Integration
          </h2>
          <p class="mb-4 text-neutral-400">
            Deploy your agents as Slack or Discord bots, enabling team members
            and community users to interact with your AI agents directly in
            their favorite chat platforms. This is different from notification
            channels—bots are interactive agents that respond to user messages.
          </p>
          <div class="mb-4 space-y-4 text-sm text-neutral-400">
            <div>
              <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-100 mb-2">
                Slack Bot Integration
              </h3>
              <p class="mb-2">
                Deploy agents as Slack bots that respond to mentions and direct
                messages. Create integrations that connect your agents to Slack
                workspaces with full support for mentions, commands, and direct
                messages.
              </p>
              <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-1 ml-4 mb-2">
                <li>Dynamic Slack App Manifest generation for easy setup</li>
                <li>Secure webhook handling with signature verification</li>
                <li>Throttled message updates for streaming-like experience</li>
                <li>Support for both channel mentions and direct messages</li>
                <li>Unified management from Integrations page</li>
              </ul>
              <p class="text-xs text-neutral-500 mt-2">
                See the Slack Integration guide for detailed setup instructions.
              </p>
            </div>
            <div>
              <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-100 mb-2">
                Discord Bot Integration
              </h3>
              <p class="mb-2">
                Deploy agents as Discord bots with slash command support. Create
                integrations that connect your agents to Discord servers with
                full support for Discord's interaction system.
              </p>
              <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-1 ml-4 mb-2">
                <li>Ed25519 signature verification for secure interactions</li>
                <li>Throttled message updates for real-time responses</li>
                <li>Full support for Discord's interaction system</li>
                <li>Slash command support</li>
                <li>Unified management from Integrations page</li>
              </ul>
              <p class="text-xs text-neutral-500 mt-2">
                See the Discord Integration guide for detailed setup
                instructions.
              </p>
            </div>
            <div>
              <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-100 mb-2">
                Key Features
              </h3>
              <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-1 ml-4">
                <li>
                  <strong>Unified Management:</strong> Manage all integrations
                  from a single Integrations page
